        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="4,27,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="In order to explain character escapes, we need a little bit of a background about literals. literals are values that are interpreted exactly as it is written."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="An exception to literals are character escapes. these are sequences that start with a backslash (\) followed by one or more characters."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="these character escapes allow the use of a special notation to represent a specific character or a control character."/></TextBlock>

